Duy Tan University: Duy Tân University (Vietnamese: Trường Đại học Duy Tân) is a private research university in Da Nang, Vietnam.[1] The name derives from the Modernisation Movement, or phong trào Duy Tân, of 1906–1908.[2]  In 2019, the school was awarded the "First Class Labor Medal" ("Huân chương Lao động hạng Nhất").[3]
